        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:48PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 748 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Idabel, or 24 miles west of Horatio, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Idabel, Broken Bow, Haworth and Holly Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
